//@version=5

// ╔═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
// ║                                                                           ║
// ║   ⚡ GOD MODE v0.7.7 - QUAD CONSENSUS TRADING SYSTEM ⚡                  ║
// ║                                                                           ║
// ║   A sophisticated multi-system consensus indicator that combines          ║
// ║   four independent trading algorithms to generate high-probability        ║
// ║   trading signals with built-in risk management.                          ║
// ║                                                                           ║
// ╠═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣
// ║                                                                           ║
// ║   SYSTEMS INCLUDED:                                                       ║
// ║   ├─ 🧠 AtroNox AI    : Bollinger Band breakout system with trend         ║
// ║   │                     detection and multi-filter options                ║
// ║   ├─ 🦅 RAPTOR Pro    : SuperTrend-based momentum system with             ║
// ║   │                     EMA cloud and reversal detection                  ║
// ║   ├─ 🎯 Scalper X     : Fast SuperTrend scalping system with              ║
// ║   │                     ADX-based market condition detection              ║
// ║   └─ 🏆 Elite Algo    : Range filter system for trend confirmation        ║
// ║                                                                           ║
// ╠═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣
// ║                                                                           ║
// ║   HOW IT WORKS:                                                           ║
// ║   • Each system independently analyzes the market                         ║
// ║   • GOD MODE signal triggers when minimum systems agree                   ║
// ║   • Signal strength calculated from consensus + market conditions         ║
// ║   • ATR-based targets (TP1, TP2, TP3) and stop loss auto-calculated       ║
// ║   • Performance tracking with win/loss statistics                         ║
// ║                                                                           ║
// ╠═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣
// ║                                                                           ║
// ║   WIN/LOSS LOGIC:                                                         ║
// ║   • TP3 Hit           → WIN (trade closed at full target)                 ║
// ║   • TP2 Hit → then SL → WIN (secured profits at TP2)                      ║
// ║   • TP1 Hit → then SL → LOSS (insufficient profit)                        ║
// ║   • No TP → SL        → LOSS (stopped out)                                ║
// ║                                                                           ║
// ║   NOTE: When both TP and SL levels are breached on the same candle,       ║
// ║   the stop loss is evaluated first (worst-case assumption).               ║
// ║                                                                           ║
// ║   NOTE: Entry is taken at bar close. TP/SL evaluation begins on the       ║
// ║   bar AFTER entry — the entry bar's own high/low printed before the       ║
// ║   entry existed and is never used (no lookahead).                         ║
// ║                                                                           ║
// ╠═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣
// ║                                                                           ║
// ║   QUICK START:                                                            ║
// ║   1. Select a Configuration Preset (Conservative/Balanced/Aggressive)     ║
// ║   2. Enable/disable individual systems as needed                          ║
// ║   3. Adjust risk management settings (TP/SL multipliers)                  ║
// ║   4. Set up alerts for GOD MODE signals                                   ║
// ║                                                                           ║
// ╠═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣
// ║                                                                           ║
// ║   RECOMMENDED SETTINGS:                                                   ║
// ║   • Timeframes: 15m, 1H, 4H (best results)                                ║
// ║   • Markets: Forex, Crypto, Indices, Commodities                          ║
// ║   • Min Systems: 2-3 for more signals, 4 for highest quality              ║
// ║   • Signal Strength: 60%+ recommended                                     ║
// ║                                                                           ║
// ╚═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝
//
// ⚠️ DISCLAIMER:
// This indicator is for educational and informational purposes only.
// It does not constitute financial advice. Trading involves substantial
// risk of loss. Past performance is not indicative of future results.
// Always conduct your own analysis and use proper risk management.
// Never risk more than you can afford to lose.
//
// 📝 CHANGELOG:
// v0.7.7 - DrFX Quant scoreboard integration (no visual/logic change)
//        - ADDED: A unique per-trade id (godTradeId) is stamped at entry from
//          syminfo.ticker + the entry bar's time, and the id of a trade closed
//          by replacement / invalidation / trailing stop is preserved
//          (closedTradeId) so its closing alert carries the correct id.
//        - ADDED: Every trade-relevant alert (entry long/short, TP1, TP2, TP3,
//          SL, trailing-stop, invalidation, replacement) now appends a hidden,
//          machine-readable tag of the form [[DRFX]]{...json...}[[/DRFX]] after
//          the version footer. The DrFX Quant server parses this tag to drive
//          its live signal scoreboard, then STRIPS it before posting, so the
//          Telegram / channel message is byte-for-byte unchanged. Entry tags
//          carry the full level set + verdict-bearing terminal events (the
//          server trusts the indicator's own TP2=win rule). Individual-system
//          alerts are deliberately left untagged (they are not trades).
//        - ADDED (0.7.7 rev): An optional "Stream / Alert ID" input. When set,
//          its value is prepended to this chart's trade IDs INSIDE the hidden
//          tag only (channel text unchanged), so multiple alerts on the SAME
//          symbol AND timeframe can be told apart on the scoreboard. Different
//          symbols and timeframes are already distinguished automatically.
//        - No indicator math, plots, dashboard, or alert *text* were changed in
//          this release (the new input only affects the hidden tag's ID).
//
// v0.7.6 - Consensus & scoring honesty pass
//        - FIXED: Signal-strength trend term was a flat +20 on nearly every
//          signal (atronoxTrend is ±1 after the first band touch) and did not
//          check direction — a counter-trend short scored the same bonus as a
//          with-trend long. The bonus is now awarded only when the trend
//          agrees with the signal's direction. NOTE: this can lower some
//          scores below the Minimum Signal Strength threshold, so expect
//          slightly fewer (and better-aligned) signals than v0.7.5.
//        - FIXED: A single system that whipsawed (fired long then short, or
//          vice-versa, inside one lookback window) was counted on BOTH the
//          long and short consensus tallies. Each system now contributes to at
//          most one side — whichever direction it signalled most recently.
//        - CHANGED: The dashboard performance block is relabelled
//          "SESSION TALLY (not a track record)". The win/loss counts are a
//          live tally accumulated from the history currently loaded on the
//          chart since the script was added; they are NOT a verified backtest
//          and depend on timeframe, loaded bars, and settings. See the release
//          notes regarding performance claims before publishing.
//
// v0.7.5 - Backtest integrity & signal-channel reliability release
//        - FIXED (critical): Entry-bar lookahead — TP/SL checks ran on the
//          entry bar against highs/lows that printed BEFORE the close-based
//          entry existed, inflating win statistics. Trade management now
//          begins on the bar after entry (godEntryBar guard).
//        - FIXED (critical): Entry alerts now use alert.freq_once_per_bar_close.
//          Previously, intrabar consensus that disappeared by bar close still
//          sent Telegram signals that never appeared on the chart or in the
//          stats. TP/SL hit alerts remain once_per_bar (a level touch is real
//          and should be reported immediately).
//        - FIXED (critical): A new GOD MODE signal arriving while a trade was
//          still open silently destroyed the open trade — it was never counted
//          as a win or loss, so totalSignals drifted away from W+L. Open
//          trades are now resolved by the TP2 rule and announced via a
//          "♻️ TRADE CLOSED — NEW SIGNAL" alert before being replaced.
//        - FIXED (critical): Dashboard table is now cleared on each render.
//          Stale "ACTIVE TRADE" rows previously remained visible after a
//          trade closed and the layout shrank.
//        - ADDED: Close alerts for trailing-stop exits and signal
//          invalidation (previously these closed trades silently — channel
//          subscribers received an entry signal and then nothing).
//        - FIXED: Trailing stop lookahead — the stop was raised using the
//          current bar's high and the SAME bar's low was then tested against
//          the freshly raised stop. Exits are now tested against the prior
//          stop before it is moved; no exit check on the activation bar.
//        - FIXED: Same-bar dual consensus tiebreak — when both directions
//          reach consensus on one bar, the side with more agreeing systems
//          wins (short no longer wins purely by code order; ties favor long).
//        - FIXED: A signal can no longer be invalidated on its own entry bar.
//        - CHANGED: Custom default targets aligned with the Balanced preset
//          (TP3 5.0, SL 1.0 ATR). The previous Custom SL default of 8.0 ATR
//          contradicted the documentation and produced inverted risk geometry.
//        - CHANGED: Minimum Systems Required is auto-clamped to the number of
//          currently enabled systems — the Conservative preset (4 systems) no
//          longer produces zero signals while AtroNox ships disabled.
//        - CHANGED: Pip factor now auto-derives from the symbol's mintick
//          (10 ticks = 1 pip convention) with a manual override; moved into
//          the Risk Management group (was hardcoded for XAUUSD in a stray
//          "Targets" group).
//        - REMOVED dead compute: unused EMA-high array (4 EMAs), 16-element
//          SMA array (only SMA-9 was read), unused minor TP signal and its
//          constants, fixed-value scalper sensitivity var, unused ocAvg and
//          color constants.
//        - CLEANED: removed deprecated transp= argument on Elite filter plot,
//          removed redundant Elite bar-color toggle (mode selector is enough),
//          dashboard entry price now uses chart precision (format.mintick),
//          corrected shorttitle version string (was v0.7.41).
//
// v0.7.4 - Input validation hotfix
//        - Removed runtime.error for TP order validation — it fired on every
//          bar, so any mid-edit transient state (e.g. typing a new TP2 value
//          before TP3 is updated) caused an immediate script crash.
//        - Removed runtime.error for SL >= TP1 validation (same reason, and
//          wide-SL / tight-TP1 setups are legitimate in certain strategies).
//        - Replaced both with silent clamping: TP2 is auto-floored to
//          TP1 + 0.1 ATR, TP3 auto-floored to TP2 + 0.1 ATR. Values on
//          chart always remain geometrically valid without ever erroring.
//        - No logic or visual changes beyond validation handling.
//
// v0.7.3 - Public release hardening
//        - Fixed critical bug: TP/SL alert direction strings showing "—"
//          Added godLastDirection variable cached at signal creation time.
//        - Fixed: Signal invalidation now resets all TP/SL hit flags.
//        - Removed dead code: cleanupTrade() stub function.
//        - Removed unused variables: sma4/5_strongScalper, isNormal.
//        - Added na() guard on volatilityRatio division.
//        - Added na() guard on dashboard calcRisk division.
//        - Updated all individual alert footers to v0.7.3.
//
// v0.7.2 - Telegram Signal Channel Integration
//        - Reformatted all alert() messages for Telegram readability
//        - Professional signal layout with emoji structure
//        - TP/SL hit alerts include trade context
//        - Individual system alerts with clean formatting
//        - Added system breakdown to GOD MODE signal alerts
//
// v0.7.1 - Bug fixes & public release preparation
//        - Fixed duplicate title parameter in RAPTOR Reversal input
//        - Fixed tp_sell/tp_buy signal variables to reset per bar
//        - Removed unused variables (pivotHigh/Low, rr1/rr3 in alerts)
//        - Updated deprecated input() calls to input.bool()/input.source()
//        - Removed unimplemented Order Block and S/R inputs
//        - Unified barcolor() into single priority-based call
//        - Removed precision=0 to use chart default precision
//        - Added same-bar TP/SL conflict documentation
//        - Replaced signalInWindow() with explicit var tracking
//
// v0.7 - Quad Consensus System with enhanced dashboard
//      - Added 4-system consensus logic
//      - Signal strength calculation
//      - Volatility filtering
//      - Performance tracking
//      - Multiple dashboard themes
//      - Trailing stop functionality
//
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

indicator("GOD MODE - Quad Consensus",
  shorttitle="⚡GOD MODE v0.7.7⚡",
  overlay=true,
  max_bars_back=3000,
  max_labels_count=500,
  max_lines_count=500,
  max_boxes_count=500,
  explicit_plot_zorder=true)

// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// ⚙️ QUICK SETUP - CONFIGURATION PRESETS
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

presetMode = input.string("Custom", "📋 Configuration Preset",
     options=["Custom", "Conservative", "Balanced", "Aggressive", "Scalping"],
     group='⚙️ QUICK SETUP',
     tooltip='Select a preset to automatically configure settings:\n\n• Conservative: High quality signals, wider stops, requires all 4 systems\n• Balanced: Standard settings, requires 3 systems\n• Aggressive: More signals, tighter stops\n• Scalping: Quick trades, small targets, requires 2 systems\n• Custom: Manual configuration')

// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// ⚡ GOD MODE CONFIGURATION
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

godModeEnabled = input.bool(true, title='✨ Enable GOD Mode Signals', group='🔥 GOD MODE SETTINGS',
     tooltip='Master switch for consensus signals. When enabled, shows signals only when multiple systems agree on direction.')

godModeWindow_input = input.int(10, title='📊 Consensus Window (Candles)', minval=3, maxval=10, group='🔥 GOD MODE SETTINGS',
     tooltip='Number of candles to look back for signal consensus. Larger window = more flexible timing but potentially delayed signals.')

godModeMinSystems_input = input.int(2, title='🎯 Minimum Systems Required', minval=1, maxval=4, group='🔥 GOD MODE SETTINGS',
     tooltip='Minimum number of systems that must agree for a GOD MODE signal:\n• 2 = More signals, lower quality\n• 3 = Balanced approach\n• 4 = Highest quality, fewer signals\n\nNote: automatically clamped to the number of currently ENABLED systems.')

minSignalStrength_input = input.float(60.0, "💪 Minimum Signal Strength %", minval=0, maxval=100, step=5, group='🔥 GOD MODE SETTINGS',
     tooltip='Minimum quality score for signals (0-100). Higher values = fewer but better quality signals. Considers system count, volatility, RSI, and trend.')

showIndividualSignals = input.bool(false, title='📌 Show Individual System Signals', group='🔥 GOD MODE SETTINGS',
     tooltip='Display signals from each individual system on the chart. Useful for analysis but can clutter the chart.')

// Apply presets
int godModeWindow     = presetMode == "Conservative" ? 3 : presetMode == "Balanced" ? 5 : presetMode == "Aggressive" ? 7 : presetMode == "Scalping" ? 4 : godModeWindow_input
// [v0.7.5] Made the Aggressive branch explicit — it previously resolved to 3
//          only by falling through to the trailing default, which was fragile.
int godModeMinSystems = presetMode == "Conservative" ? 4 : presetMode == "Balanced" ? 3 : presetMode == "Aggressive" ? 3 : presetMode == "Scalping" ? 2 : godModeMinSystems_input
float minSignalStrength = presetMode == "Conservative" ? 70.0 : presetMode == "Balanced" ? 60.0 : presetMode == "Aggressive" ? 50.0 : presetMode == "Scalping" ? 55.0 : minSignalStrength_input

useVolatilityFilter = input.bool(true, "🌊 Volatility Filter", group='🔥 GOD MODE SETTINGS', inline='vol1',
     tooltip='Filter signals based on market volatility. Helps avoid trading in unfavorable conditions.')
minVolatility = input.float(0.8, "Min", group='🔥 GOD MODE SETTINGS', inline='vol1', tooltip='Minimum ATR ratio - avoid low volatility')
maxVolatility = input.float(2.5, "Max", group='🔥 GOD MODE SETTINGS', inline='vol1', tooltip='Maximum ATR ratio - avoid extreme volatility')

useSignalTimeout = input.bool(true, "⏱️ Signal Invalidation", group='🔥 GOD MODE SETTINGS', inline='timeout',
     tooltip='Invalidate position if opposing signal appears. Helps exit trades when market direction changes.')
signalTimeout = input.int(10, "bars", minval=3, maxval=30, group='🔥 GOD MODE SETTINGS', inline='timeout')

// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// 🎯 RISK MANAGEMENT
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

godTargetsEnabled = input.bool(true, title='🎯 Enable Target System', group='🎯 RISK MANAGEMENT',
     tooltip='Show ATR-based take profit levels and stop loss on chart.')

godTargetATRLength = input.int(14, title='ATR Period', minval=1, group='🎯 RISK MANAGEMENT',
     tooltip='ATR calculation period for targets. Standard is 14.')

godTP1_Multiplier_input = input.float(1.5, title='🥉 Target 1 (ATR)', minval=0.1, step=0.1, group='🎯 RISK MANAGEMENT',
     tooltip='First take profit level. Conservative target for partial profits.')

godTP2_Multiplier_input = input.float(3.0, title='🥈 Target 2 (ATR)', minval=0.2, step=0.1, group='🎯 RISK MANAGEMENT',
     tooltip='Second take profit level. Moderate target - reaching this counts as WIN even if stopped out after.')

// [v0.7.5] Custom defaults aligned with the Balanced preset (TP3 was 8.0).
godTP3_Multiplier_input = input.float(8.0, title='🥇 Target 3 (ATR)', minval=0.3, step=0.5, group='🎯 RISK MANAGEMENT',
     tooltip='Full take profit level. Aggressive target for maximum gains.')

// [v0.7.5] Default was 8.0 ATR — wider than TP3 and contradicting the docs.
//          Tooltip reworded: since v0.7.4 SL >= TP1 is allowed (clamping
//          removed the hard validation), but it produces poor risk geometry.
godSL_Multiplier_input = input.float(8.0, title='🛡️ Stop Loss (ATR)', minval=0.1, step=0.1, group='🎯 RISK MANAGEMENT',
     tooltip='Stop loss distance from entry in ATR multiples. Values larger than TP1 are allowed but produce poor risk:reward geometry — review the R:R shown on the dashboard before trading.')

// Apply presets to targets
float godTP1_Multiplier = presetMode == "Conservative" ? 2.0 : presetMode == "Balanced" ? 1.5 : presetMode == "Aggressive" ? 1.2 : presetMode == "Scalping" ? 0.8 : godTP1_Multiplier_input
float godTP2_Multiplier = presetMode == "Conservative" ? 4.0 : presetMode == "Balanced" ? 3.0 : presetMode == "Aggressive" ? 2.5 : presetMode == "Scalping" ? 1.5 : godTP2_Multiplier_input
float godTP3_Multiplier = presetMode == "Conservative" ? 6.0 : presetMode == "Balanced" ? 5.0 : presetMode == "Aggressive" ? 4.0 : presetMode == "Scalping" ? 2.5 : godTP3_Multiplier_input
float godSL_Multiplier  = presetMode == "Conservative" ? 1.5 : presetMode == "Balanced" ? 1.0 : presetMode == "Aggressive" ? 0.8 : presetMode == "Scalping" ? 0.5 : godSL_Multiplier_input

// ── Ensure valid target ordering via silent clamping ──────────────────────
// [v0.7.4] Replaced runtime.error with clamping. runtime.error fires on
//          every bar, so any mid-edit transient invalid state caused a crash.
//          Clamping silently enforces TP1 < TP2 < TP3 without ever erroring.
float safeTP1 = godTP1_Multiplier
float safeTP2 = math.max(godTP2_Multiplier, safeTP1 + 0.1)
float safeTP3 = math.max(godTP3_Multiplier, safeTP2 + 0.1)
godTP1_Multiplier := safeTP1
godTP2_Multiplier := safeTP2
godTP3_Multiplier := safeTP3

godSLEnabled = input.bool(true, "🛡️ Enable Stop Loss", group='🎯 RISK MANAGEMENT',
     tooltip='⚠️ DISABLING STOP LOSS IS NOT RECOMMENDED! Only disable for backtesting purposes.')

useTrailingStop = input.bool(false, "🔒 Enable Trailing Stop", group='🎯 RISK MANAGEMENT',
     tooltip='Activate trailing stop after price moves favorably. Locks in profits as trade moves in your favor.')

trailActivation = input.float(3.5, "Trail Activation (ATR)", minval=0.5, step=0.1, group='🎯 RISK MANAGEMENT',
     tooltip='Price must move this far in profit before trailing activates.')

trailDistance = input.float(3.0, "Trail Distance (ATR)", minval=0.3, step=0.1, group='🎯 RISK MANAGEMENT',
     tooltip='Distance to maintain behind price once trailing is active.')

showTargetLines  = input.bool(true,  title='Show Target Lines',   group='🎯 RISK MANAGEMENT', inline='visual1')
showTargetLabels = input.bool(true,  title='Show Labels',         group='🎯 RISK MANAGEMENT', inline='visual1')
extendTargetLines = input.bool(false, title='Extend Lines Right',  group='🎯 RISK MANAGEMENT')

targetLineStyle = input.string('Dotted', title='Line Style', options=['Solid', 'Dashed', 'Dotted'], group='🎯 RISK MANAGEMENT')
targetLineWidth = input.int(1, title='Line Width', minval=1, maxval=4, group='🎯 RISK MANAGEMENT')

// ---- Pip Conversion ----
// [v0.7.5] Auto-derived from the symbol's mintick using the standard
//          "10 ticks = 1 pip" convention (correct for forex and metals;
//          equivalent to points/10 elsewhere). Previously hardcoded for
//          XAUUSD in a stray "Targets" settings group.
autoPipFactor = input.bool(true, "Auto Pip Factor (10 ticks = 1 pip)", group='🎯 RISK MANAGEMENT',
     tooltip='Derive pip size from the symbol automatically. Disable to use the manual factor below.')
pipFactorManual = input.float(10.0, "Manual Pip Factor", minval=0.0001, group='🎯 RISK MANAGEMENT',
     tooltip='Used only when Auto Pip Factor is off.\nExamples: XAUUSD = 10, EURUSD = 10000, USDJPY = 100.')

colorTP1   = input.color(color.new(#00ff00, 20), title='TP1',       group='🎯 RISK MANAGEMENT', inline='colors1')
colorTP2   = input.color(color.new(#ffff00, 20), title='TP2',       group='🎯 RISK MANAGEMENT', inline='colors1')
colorTP3   = input.color(color.new(#ff6600, 20), title='TP3',       group='🎯 RISK MANAGEMENT', inline='colors2')
colorEntry = input.color(color.new(#ffffff, 30), title='Entry',     group='🎯 RISK MANAGEMENT', inline='colors2')
colorSL    = input.color(color.new(#ff0000, 20), title='Stop Loss', group='🎯 RISK MANAGEMENT', inline='colors3')
colorTrail = input.color(color.new(#ff9900, 30), title='Trail Stop',group='🎯 RISK MANAGEMENT', inline='colors3')

alertOnTP1 = input.bool(true, title='Alert TP1', group='🎯 RISK MANAGEMENT', inline='alerts1')
alertOnTP2 = input.bool(true, title='Alert TP2', group='🎯 RISK MANAGEMENT', inline='alerts1')
alertOnTP3 = input.bool(true, title='Alert TP3', group='🎯 RISK MANAGEMENT', inline='alerts2')
alertOnSL  = input.bool(true, title='Alert SL',  group='🎯 RISK MANAGEMENT', inline='alerts2')

// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// 🧠 ATRONOX SYSTEM SETTINGS
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

atronoxEnabled = input.bool(false, title='✅ Enable AtroNox System', group='🧠 ATRONOX SETTINGS',
     tooltip='Bollinger Band breakout system with trend detection. Uses price breakouts above/below bands to identify trend changes.')

showAtronoxLongSignals  = input.bool(true, title='Long Signals',  group='🧠 ATRONOX SETTINGS', inline='atronox1')
showAtronoxShortSignals = input.bool(true, title='Short Signals', group='🧠 ATRONOX SETTINGS', inline='atronox1')

selectedFilterAtronox = input.string('No Filtering', title='Market Filter',
     options=['Filter with ATR', 'Filter with RSI', 'ATR or RSI', 'ATR and RSI', 'No Filtering', 'Entry Only in Flat Market (ATR or RSI)', 'Entry Only in Flat Market (ATR and RSI)'],
     group='🧠 ATRONOX SETTINGS',
     tooltip='Additional filtering for entry conditions based on ATR and/or RSI.')

atronoxSensitivity = input.int(100, minval=1, title='Sensitivity', group='🧠 ATRONOX SETTINGS',
     tooltip='Bollinger Band period. Higher = smoother, lower = more responsive.')

atronoxOffset = input.float(1.5, step=0.01, minval=0.01, title='Offset', group='🧠 ATRONOX SETTINGS',
     tooltip='Bollinger Band standard deviation multiplier.')

rsiPeriodAtronox    = input.int(7,  title='RSI Period', group='🧠 ATRONOX SETTINGS')
rsiUpperLimitAtronox = input.int(45, title='RSI Upper', group='🧠 ATRONOX SETTINGS', inline='rsi1')
rsiLowerLimitAtronox = input.int(10, title='Lower',     group='🧠 ATRONOX SETTINGS', inline='rsi1')

atrLengthAtronox   = input.int(5, minval=1, title='ATR Length',  group='🧠 ATRONOX SETTINGS')
atrMaTypeAtronox   = input.string('EMA', options=['SMA', 'EMA'], title='ATR MA Type', group='🧠 ATRONOX SETTINGS', inline='atr1')
atrMaLengthAtronox = input.int(5, minval=1, title='MA Length',   group='🧠 ATRONOX SETTINGS', inline='atr1')

showBandsAtronox    = input.bool(false, title='Show Bollinger Bands', group='🧠 ATRONOX SETTINGS', inline='visual1')
showTrendLineAtronox = input.bool(false, title='Show Trend Line',     group='🧠 ATRONOX SETTINGS', inline='visual1')
showZonesAtronox    = input.bool(false, title='Show Trading Zones',   group='🧠 ATRONOX SETTINGS')

// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// 🦅 RAPTOR SYSTEM SETTINGS
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

raptorEnabled = input.bool(true, title='✅ Enable RAPTOR System', group='🦅 RAPTOR SETTINGS',
     tooltip='SuperTrend-based momentum system. Identifies trend changes when price crosses the SuperTrend line with SMA confirmation.')

sensitivityRaptor = input.float(6.5, "SuperTrend Sensitivity", 0.5, 12, step=0.05, group='🦅 RAPTOR SETTINGS',
     tooltip='SuperTrend ATR multiplier. Higher = fewer signals, lower = more signals.')

showSMARaptor      = input.bool(false, 'SMA Bands',      inline='raptor1', group='🦅 RAPTOR SETTINGS')
majRaptor          = input.bool(false, 'TP Points',      inline='raptor1', group='🦅 RAPTOR SETTINGS')
showEMARaptor      = input.bool(false, 'EMA Cloud',      inline='raptor2', group='🦅 RAPTOR SETTINGS')
enableReversalRaptor = input.bool(false, 'Reversal Signal', inline='raptor2', group='🦅 RAPTOR SETTINGS')
show_haRaptor      = input.bool(false, 'Trend Tracker',  inline='raptor3', group='🦅 RAPTOR SETTINGS')
enableSRRaptor     = input.bool(false, 'S/R Levels',     inline='raptor3', group='🦅 RAPTOR SETTINGS')
Show_TBORaptor     = input.bool(false, 'Show TBO',       inline='raptor4', group='🦅 RAPTOR SETTINGS')
Show_SuperIchiRaptor = input.bool(false, 'SuperIchi Cloud', inline='raptor4', group='🦅 RAPTOR SETTINGS')

BLuERaptor  = input.color(color.rgb(95,155,245,0),   'Up Trend',   group='🦅 RAPTOR - SMA Settings', inline='sma1')
GRayRaptor  = input.color(color.rgb(160,165,185,0),  'Down Trend', group='🦅 RAPTOR - SMA Settings', inline='sma1')
BFiLLRaptor = input.color(color.rgb(95,155,245,60),  'Up Fill',    group='🦅 RAPTOR - SMA Settings', inline='sma2')
GFiLLRaptor = input.color(color.rgb(160,165,185,40), 'Down Fill',  group='🦅 RAPTOR - SMA Settings', inline='sma2')

fastLenRaptor    = input.int(34, 'Fast EMA Length', group='🦅 RAPTOR - EMA Cloud', minval=1)
slowLenRaptor    = input.int(63, 'Slow EMA Length', group='🦅 RAPTOR - EMA Cloud', minval=1)
emaFastColorRaptor = input.color(color.blue,   'Fast EMA Color', group='🦅 RAPTOR - EMA Cloud')
emaSlowColorRaptor = input.color(color.orange, 'Slow EMA Color', group='🦅 RAPTOR - EMA Cloud')

custom_tboRaptor  = input.bool(false, "Enable Custom Periods", group="🦅 RAPTOR - TBO Settings")
tbo_fastRaptor    = input.int(20,  "TBO Fast EMA",   1, group="🦅 RAPTOR - TBO Settings")
tbo_mediumRaptor  = input.int(40,  "TBO Medium EMA", 2, group="🦅 RAPTOR - TBO Settings")
tbo_medfastRaptor = input.int(50,  "TBO Med-Fast SMA", 3, group="🦅 RAPTOR - TBO Settings")
tbo_slowRaptor    = input.int(150, "TBO Slow SMA",   4, group="🦅 RAPTOR - TBO Settings")

use_rsiRaptor          = input.bool(false,        "Enable RSI Filter",  group="🦅 RAPTOR - TBO RSI")
short_rsi_levelRaptor  = input.int(70,  "Short RSI Level", 1, 100, group="🦅 RAPTOR - TBO RSI")
short_comparisonRaptor = input.string("Greater Than", "Short Condition", ["Greater Than", "Less Than"], group="🦅 RAPTOR - TBO RSI")
long_rsi_levelRaptor   = input.int(30,  "Long RSI Level",  1, 100, group="🦅 RAPTOR - TBO RSI")
long_comparisonRaptor  = input.string("Less Than",    "Long Condition",  ["Greater Than", "Less Than"], group="🦅 RAPTOR - TBO RSI")
rsi_periodRaptor       = input.int(14,  "RSI Period", 1, group="🦅 RAPTOR - TBO RSI")

reversal_sensitivityRaptor  = input.int(14, title="Reversal Sensitivity", minval=1, group="🦅 RAPTOR - Reversal")
reversal_down_levelRaptor   = input.int(75, 'Reversal Down Level', group='🦅 RAPTOR - Reversal')
reversal_up_levelRaptor     = input.int(25, 'Reversal Up Level',   group='🦅 RAPTOR - Reversal')

sr_strengthRaptor    = input.int(4, "S/R Strength", 1, group="🦅 RAPTOR - S/R")
line_style_srRaptor  = input.string("Solid", "Line Style", ["Solid", "Dotted", "Dashed"], group="🦅 RAPTOR - S/R")
use_zones_srRaptor   = input.bool(true, "Show S/R Zones", group="🦅 RAPTOR - S/R")

macd_fastRaptor   = input.int(12, "MACD Fast Length",  group="🦅 RAPTOR - Candle Color")
macd_slowRaptor   = input.int(26, "MACD Slow Length",  group="🦅 RAPTOR - Candle Color")
macd_sourceRaptor = input.source(close, "MACD Source", group="🦅 RAPTOR - Candle Color")
macd_signalRaptor = input.int(9,  "Signal Smoothing", 1, 50, group="🦅 RAPTOR - Candle Color")

// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// 🎯 SCALPER SYSTEM SETTINGS
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

scalperEnabled = input.bool(true, title='✅ Enable Scalper System', group='🎯 SCALPER SETTINGS',
     tooltip='Fast SuperTrend scalping system. Designed for quick entries with ADX-based sideways market detection.')

nbuysellScalper = input.bool(true, 'Show Signals', group='🎯 SCALPER SETTINGS')

sidewaysThresholdScalper = input.int(15, 'ADX Sideways Threshold', minval=2, group='🎯 SCALPER SETTINGS',
     tooltip='ADX level below which market is considered sideways. Bars turn purple in sideways markets.')

// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// 🏆 ELITE ALGO SYSTEM SETTINGS
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

eliteEnabled = input.bool(true, title='✅ Enable Elite Algo System', group='🏆 ELITE ALGO SETTINGS',
     tooltip='Range filter system for trend confirmation. Uses dynamic range calculations to identify trend direction changes.')

rng_src = input.source(defval=close, title='Swing Source', group='🏆 ELITE ALGO SETTINGS')
rng_per = input.int(defval=200, minval=1, title='Swing Period', group='🏆 ELITE ALGO SETTINGS',
     tooltip='Lookback period for range calculation. Higher = smoother.')

rng_qty = input.float(defval=7.5, minval=0.0000001, title='Swing Multiplier', group='🏆 ELITE ALGO SETTINGS',
     tooltip='Range multiplier. Higher = wider range, fewer signals.')

showEliteFilter    = input.bool(false, title='Show Range Filter Line',  group='🏆 ELITE ALGO SETTINGS')

// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
